               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus letter from the Herakleopolites(?) (Heracleopolite Nome), Egypt in which Lochos strategos, a high official and maybe the strategos of the Thebaid of ca. 127-117 B.C., informs Ariston strategos and nomarches, a high civil and army official involved in taxation and one of the first friends of the king, about some official business related to soldiers</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 13.6 cm. x 18.0 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">10 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto; written along the fibers on the verso in a different hand, the address in large letters inverse to the text on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 3.5 cm.; lower margin of 3.5 cm.; left margin of 4 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">Extracted from mummy cartonnage with P.Duk.inv. 324-327 and P.Duk.inv. 329-434</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 328 was formerly P.Duk.inv. AF74 5</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
